title: Coinbase Hit With SEC Suit That Identifies $37 Billion Of Crypto Tokens As Securities
author: Emily Mason
description: Agency follows up on Binance complaint with case that accuses largest U.S. crypto exchange of registration infractions, including 13 digital assets.

title: Web3 Growth Stymied By Scarcity Of Programmers
author: Nina Bambysheva
description: Developer shortage stands in the way of decentralized, blockchain-centric internet bliss.

title: Web3 Projects Are Rebuilding Carbon Offsets’ Architecture Of Trust
author: Alan Ransil
description: A set of Web3 tools are converging to enable better systems for publicly verifying forest protection, allowing offsets to be tied directly to data about the forests they are protecting.

title: Creators Of Andreessen Horowitz-Backed Cryptocurrency Filecoin Fires 21% Of Staff After Raising Record $205 Million
author: Michael del Castillo
description: One of Web3’s earliest pioneers, Protocol Labs, has laid off 89 people, or more than a fifth of its total staff according to documents reviewed by Forbes, provided by one of the employees, who asked not to be identified so as to not harm their future job searches.

title: Binance Coin (BNB) Loses 8% As SEC Takes Exchange To Court
author: Steven Ehrlich
description: Crypto market weakens on outlook for tougher regulation, other prominent tokens mentioned in the lawsuit fall as well.

title: Crypto Market Shrinks 2% As SEC Opens Second Front In Exchange Crackdown
author: Maria Gracia Santillana Linares
description: Coinbase shares slide 15% after agency names company in civil complaint, a day after similar action against Binance.

title: Polygon-Backed Crypto Accelerator Targets SEA, As Talents Flock To Web3
author: Joseph Young
description: Singapore-based crypto incubator Ice Tea Labs has launched a new Web3 accelerator targeting Southeast Asia.
